Endangered Species Chocolate - 5846 W 73rd St, Indianapolis, IN 46278

Possibly the best dumpster in the country! At least if you love chocolate!

voting_set.comment: Aldi: Late at night is best. It's possible to get in by the top if you pull the gate a bit. I prefer to climb by the back as it make less noise as someone living next door has been calling the cops. There is food everyday.
voting_set.name: Gerd

voting_set.comment: Andronico's Community Market: Produces a healthy lot of produce!
voting_set.name: Gerd

voting_set.comment: Utile: Boulevard de Bonnefoy, near Av de Lavaur (location is approximate, and may no longer exist). Go on Monday, Wednesday, Friday evenings when their bins are out. Around 9.30pm should be good since it's just after they close. There is usually a fare bit to find from their bins (Last checked: December 2011)
voting_set.name: Gerd

voting_set.comment: Bunnpris Steinan (Bunnpris Vestlia?) has an unlocked dumpster easily accesible on the side of the store. Vegetables, fruit and some dairy products. The store closes at 23.00.
voting_set.name: Gerd

voting_set.comment:
Coop Konsum @ HÃ¶glundagatan 17

Has an unlocked dumpster, often with wide variety of food. What is good to remember is that you should only enter the dumpsters after closing time. Folks say guys at Coop Konsum know that there are dumpster divers visiting their store dumpsters, and they are okay with it as long as it's after closing time and as long as people don't make a mess outside the dumpster. (Last checked: September 2012)
voting_set.name: Gerd

voting_set.comment: Tesco (address: 50 Montgomery Ter Rd, Sheffield S6 3BU). How to get to the bins: You need to be able to squeeze through to the left of the main gate at the deliveries part of the site. If you push the white post to the left it makes the gap bigger. The food is in the big grey container to the left. (Last checked: February 2011)
voting_set.name: Gerd

voting_set.comment: Andy's Bakery and Deli: Usually they leave bread in the back alley. As of January 2011, they stopped locking the dumpster, too.
voting_set.name: Gerd

voting_set.comment: Consum: "On Avinguda Catalunya you can dumpster dive for vegetables thrown out by Consum." No such store could be found, but perhaps it applies to this branch.
voting_set.name: Gerd

voting_set.comment: "Tesco" in Tollcross is pretty reliable, peppers, Danish pastries, bananas and curry mostly, and there are no cameras so you can easily go during the day. It is the green recycling solutions bin in the back street behind the shop It is used by many, so only take what you need. (Last checked: January 2011)
voting_set.name: Gerd
